"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056708","Home Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>As part of the overall £45.5 million package included in the Sandhurst Treaty to underpin the joint co-operation between the UK and France, we have allocated £3.6 million specifically to fund the development of the Dublin process to support transfers of eligible children to the UK (including training for those working with unaccompanied children, family tracing and targeted information campaigns). This full package of £3.6 million was paid to the French Government at the end of 2018. We continue to work with France to transfer eligible children under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 and the Dublin regulation and transfers are ongoing.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","218270","2019-02-12T12:27:05.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056708/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056708/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056708/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-07","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 6 February 2019 to Question 215158 on UK-France Migration Committee, what proportion of the £3.6 million allocated to the funding of the development of the Dublin process to support transfers of eligible children to the UK has been made in payments.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","218269"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056709","Home Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>As part of the overall £45.5 million package included in the Sandhurst Treaty to underpin the joint co-operation between the UK and France, we have allocated £3.6 million specifically to fund the development of the Dublin process to support transfers of eligible children to the UK (including training for those working with unaccompanied children, family tracing and targeted information campaigns). This full package of £3.6 million was paid to the French Government at the end of 2018. We continue to work with France to transfer eligible children under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 and the Dublin regulation and transfers are ongoing.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","218269","2019-02-12T12:27:05.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056709/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056709/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056709/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-07","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 6 February 2019 to Question 215158 on UK-France Migration Committee, how many children have been transferred as a result of the £3.6 million allocated to the funding of the development of the Dublin process.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","218270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056710","Home Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>It is Home Office policy not to comment on details of the deployment of covert assets or any operational capability or taskings, as to do so would or likely to prejudice national security.</p><p>Please see below a Home Office publication link to transparency data from 2010 to financial year 2017/2018 on Home Office spending.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ho-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ho-annual-reports-and-accounts</a></p><p><br>Border Force uses a layered approach to coastal defence, including patrols comprising additional military and law enforcement vessels, on-shore re-sources and intelligence and surveillance to detect efforts to smuggle guns and drugs or facilitate illegal entry into the country.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-02-12T12:22:24.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056710/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056710/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056710/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-07","Surveillance: English Channel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much has been spent on aerial surveillance of the English Channel in (a) each year from 2010 to 2018 and (b) 2019 to date.","false","Biography information for Charlie Elphicke","Dover","Charlie Elphicke","218271"
