rces/1056744/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-07","Electronic Cigarettes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the Seventh Report of Session 2017-19 of the Science and Technology Committee on E-cigarettes, HC505, what steps he has taken to ensure that the regulatory system for e-cigarettes is risk-proportionate.","false","Biography information for Adam Afriyie","Windsor","Adam Afriyie","218246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056745","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-02-14","<p>Selective licensing can be an effective, targeted tool to deliver improved standards and safety in the private rented sector for areas suffering from serious problems. Where selective licensing is poorly designed and not well targeted, it can come at a cost to landlords, which can be passed on to tenants through increased rents.</p><p>The Government only holds information on schemes that require the approval of the Secretary of State. Since 2015, schemes which cover more than 20 per cent of a local authority’s private rented stock or geographical area require approval. Eight schemes have been approved by the Secretary of State in the following local authority areas: Blackpool, Brent, Burnley, Hyndburn, Newham, Nottingham, Peterborough and Redbridge.</p><p>We are currently conducting an independent review into the effectiveness of selective licensing, through which we are engaging with local authorities about their experience of selective licensing. The final report is due to be published in Spring 2019.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","218308 ; 218309","2019-02-14T16:08:19.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056745/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056745/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-02-07","Private Rented Housing: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to enable more local authorities to establish selective licensing schemes in areas where they are needed to tackle poor housing conditions.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","218310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056746","Attorney General","false","2019-02-13","<p>The Attorney General’s Office, along with all of HM Government, is committed to ensuring that we make a success of EU Exit. No officials from the Attorney General’s Office, a small ministerial department, have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; officials working on EU Exit are preparing for all scenarios.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2019-02-13T16:38:57.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056746/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056746/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056746/answer",,,,,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2019-02-07","Attorney General: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218149"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056747","Cabinet Office","false","2019-02-25","<p>Departments continually review workforce plans, reprioritise and assess changing needs, which includes identification and cessation of non-priority work where appropriate. We have accelerated our plans, and at the same time, the Civil Service as a whole is working to ensure that EU Exit Implementation is carried out to high quality without impacting public service delivery across the whole of government. The Cabinet Office has staff working on EU exit implementation for a range of scenarios in the interests of preparedness, however the percentage of time spent on exiting the EU without a deal is not recorded or easily accessible at this stage.</p><p>Cabinet Office are currently looking to increase the numbers of staff trained to be part of the Civil Contingencies Secretariat to form a flexible pool to be used if and when required.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2019-02-25T11:30:10.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056747/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056747/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056747/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-02-07","Cabinet Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218150"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056748","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-02-12","<p>BEIS has established a mobilisation plan that ensures all EU Exit work, including the possibility of no deal, receives the right level of staffing. Redeployment is underway and as of 30th January, C. 350 staff had been mobilised from their primary roles to support EU Exit work.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2019-02-12T17:55:47.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056748/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056748/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056748/answer",,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-02-07","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218151"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056749","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-02-20","As part of the department’s preparations for the possibility of leaving the EU without a deal, over 110 officials have been seconded from their primary role to support EU Exit work. In addition, a significant number of officials have reprioritised their work to include EU Exit work whilst remaining in their primary roles.<p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2019-02-20T09:56:21.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056749/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056749/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056749/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-02-07","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218152"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750","Department for Education","false","2019-02-22","<p>It is the top priority of the government to leave the EU with a deal, but it is also the responsibility of government to prepare for all scenarios, including the prospect of a no deal. The Civil Service is focused on delivering the government’s most pressing priorities, so it is only sensible that we make use of the resources and expertise we have available to make sure the UK is prepared for all Brexit scenarios on exit day. This includes departments sharing staff and working together on joint projects. The number of people seconded to other government departments to support preparations for leaving the EU without a deal is 70.</p><p> </p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2019-02-22T14:17:17.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750/answer","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750/answer/previousversion/102295","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056750/answer/previousversion/102295",,,"60","Education","Education","2019-02-07","Department for Education: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056751","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-02-15","<p>Over 80% of Defra’s agenda is affected by the UK’s departure from the European Union and as a result many roles across the Defra group are now supporting work related to our departure from the EU, either directly or indirectly. We are unable to disaggregate between ‘deal’ and ‘no deal’ planning work.</p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2019-02-15T14:30:00.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056751/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056751/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056751/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-02-07","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056752","Department for International Development","false","2019-02-14","<p>DFID has deployed 26 employees on short-term loan to other government departments and fewer than 10 staff internally to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU, with or without a deal.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-02-14T16:15:56.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056752/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056752/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056752/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-02-07","Department for International Development: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many officials from her Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056753","Department for International Trade","false","2019-02-14","<p>The Department of International Trade (DIT) was created as a result of the UK’s decision to leave the European Union. All the work carried out by the Department contributes to supporting the government to deliver Brexit. Individual roles are not classified according to particular EU Exit scenarios, including leaving without a deal.</p><p> </p><p>Several teams within DIT have reprioritised their activity where necessary to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal.</p><p> </p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart",,"2019-02-14T17:46:35.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056753/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056753/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056753/answer",,,,,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2019-02-07","Department for International Trade: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056754","Department for Transport","false","2019-02-13","<p>The Department has approximately 260 Full Time Equivalent staff currently working on EU Exit. The Department does not distinguish between those working on deal and no-deal scenarios.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2019-02-13T17:16:24.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056754/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056754/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056754/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-02-07","Department for Transport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056755","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2019-02-18","<p>To date, no DWP officials have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal. DWP continues to make appropriate preparations using existing staff.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2019-02-18T17:53:20.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056755/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056755/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056755/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2019-02-07","Department for Work and Pensions: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many officials from her Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056756","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-15","<p>The United Kingdom Tobacco and Related Products Regulations 2016 (TRPR) covers the regulation of e-cigarettes transposed from the European Union’s Tobacco Products Directive. Regulation 38 of the TRPR covers product presentation requirements and defines what can be written on a unit packet and any container pack of the electronic cigarette or refill container. Products may not for example suggest that a particular electronic cigarette or refill container is less harmful than other electronic cigarettes or refill containers; has vitalising, energising, healing, rejuvenating, natural or organic properties; or has other health or lifestyle benefits. These regulations also prohibit price reductions.</p><p> </p><p>The Advertising Standards Authority (ASA) is responsible for monitoring the marketing and advertising of non-broadcast communications for electronic cigarettes. Section 22 of the ASA Committee of Advertising Practice Code concerns the regulation of marketing communications for electronic cigarettes. The code does not allow for medicinal claims but provides advice on how health claims can be made for marketing purposes that are not restricted by regulation.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has made a commitment to review the TRPR by May 2021 to consider its regulatory impact. In addition, as announced in the Tobacco Control Plan the Government will review where the UK’s exit from the EU offers us opportunities to re-appraise current regulation to ensure this continues to protect the nation’s health.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-02-15T11:08:47.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056756/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056756/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056756/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-07","Electronic Cigarettes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether companies are prevented from (a) encouraging smokers to switch to vaping and (b) advertising price reductions for e-cigarettes.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","218311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056757","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-14","<p>As at 11 February 2019, the Department has a central team of 70 policy and project delivery professionals which coordinates the provision of advice to Ministers on European Union exit and preparations for exit. Since the beginning of December 2018, 25 people have transferred into the central team to support this work.</p><p> </p><p>Across the Department, staff are also working on a range of areas related to EU exit, covering issues such as medicines supply. Communications, analytical and legal staff provide advice as required. This work is kept under review, to manage the level of resource support that may be needed at any given time.</p><p> </p><p>The Civil Service as a whole is working to ensure that EU exit implementation is carried out to a high standard without impacting public service delivery across the whole of government.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2019-02-14T12:10:57.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056757/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056757/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056757/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-07","Department of Health and Social Care: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056758","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-02-15","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) has created approximately 550 EU Exit roles in the UK and overseas to work on a range of issues including Deal and No Deal scenarios and EU Exit planning. We have used these roles to strengthen our diplomatic network in the UK and across Europe so that we are better able to represent and promote British interests and engage with our European partners in support of a successful EU Exit. In addition, other staff are also engaged on EU Exit planning as part of their wider responsibilities. The FCO continues to keep its EU Exit staffing levels under constant review to ensure that they are appropriate to deliver the Government's objectives.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2019-02-15T11:01:49.557Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056758/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056758/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056758/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-02-07","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218160"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056759","Treasury","false","2019-02-14","<p>The department regularly reprioritises work in line with its changing priorities as part of its dynamic and flexible resourcing model. Many staff will work both on EU Exit and other priorities. Because of this it is not possible to give an accurate estimate of the number of civil servants involved solely in contingency planning for ‘No Deal’, at any one time.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-02-14T17:14:44.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056759/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056759/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056759/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-02-07","Treasury: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218161"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056760","Home Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>The department has been continually assessing the resourcing levels required to prepare for Brexit across all possible scenarios, developing contingency plans in line with government policy.</p><p>It is not possible to provide an answer to the specific question asked. This is because staff are generally engaged across a range of workstreams, which will include business as usual activity as well as Brexit preparations, across both deal and no deal scenarios.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-02-12T12:15:39.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056760/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056760/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056760/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-07","Home Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218162"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056761","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-02-15","<p>It is the top priority of the Government to leave the EU with a deal, but it is also the responsibility of Government to prepare for all scenarios, including the prospect of a no deal. The Civil Service is focused on delivering the Government's most pressing priorities, so it is only sensible that we make use of the resources and expertise we have available to make sure the UK is prepared for all Brexit scenarios on exit day. This includes Departments sharing staff and working together on joint projects. The number of staff being seconded from the Ministry of Defence as part of a coordinated exercise is yet to be determined.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-02-15T14:05:24.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056761/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056761/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056761/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-02-07","Ministry of Defence: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056762","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-02-15","<p>A number of central teams have been established within the Department to lead and manage the work required to prepare for the UK's exit from the EU. These teams have been built up in a phased and gradual manner to reflect the increase in work associated with our exit from the EU. Until recently approximately 60 staff were deployed to this work, which covers all exit scenarios including a no deal scenario. We have however now redeployed a further 30 staff from their previous role to work on these central teams. Other staff from across the Department will have been redeployed within their Directorates to support or undertake work which will involve preparations for the UK's exit from the EU in all scenarios.</p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2019-02-15T11:35:28.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056762/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056762/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056762/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-02-07","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-02-22","<p>Delivering the deal negotiated with the EU remains the Government’s top priority. This has not changed.</p><p> </p><p>However, the Government must prepare for every eventuality, including a no deal scenario. As we approach 29 March, we have accelerated and intensified these preparations and at the same time, the Civil Service as a whole is working to ensure that EU Exit Implementation is carried out to high quality without impacting public service delivery across the whole of government.</p><p> </p><p>The approximate total number of people working on EU exit across the MoJ is 110. The MoJ EU exit programme includes work on both deal and no-deal scenarios in preparation for the UK exit from the EU.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2019-02-22T14:33:33.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763/answer","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763/answer/previousversion/102314","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056763/answer/previousversion/102314",,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-02-07","Ministry of Justice: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many officials from his Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056764","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>EU exit affects a number of work areas across the Department and will therefore encompass a proportion of workload for many staff, the amount of which will vary over time. The Department has restructured its approach to the way it handles EU exit work, moving from a central EU exit co-ordinating team of 7 to a position in which core EU exit work is distributed more widely across the whole department. No officials have been seconded in the way this question asks.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2019-02-12T11:09:15.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056764/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056764/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056764/answer",,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-02-07","Northern Ireland Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many officials from her Department have been seconded from their primary role to make preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a deal; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","218166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056765","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-12","<p>All National Health Service dental practices are required to display a poster showing patient charges and to offer patients a free leaflet which sets out in detail who is entitled to free NHS dental services. Information on exemptions and support for people who are on a low income can also be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/healthcosts" target="_blank">www.nhs.uk/healthcosts</a></p><p> </p><p>Eligibility checks are carried out on claims received for exemption from NHS Dental Patient Charges. Where eligibility cannot be verified, patients are asked to confirm their eligibility or to pay the relevant dental charge plus a penalty charge. Patients are, however, able to challenge penalty charges they believe are unjustified.</p><p> </p><p>The Department, NHS Business Services Authority and NHS England have recognised the concern that some patients may not be clear on whether they are exempt from charges and has been working to further improve the information available to patients around eligibility. This includes promoting an easy read patient information booklet, creating an online eligibility checker and developing a national awareness campaign.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","218313","2019-02-12T15:25:29.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056765/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056765/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056765/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-07","Dental Services: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the press release entitled, Dentists welcome official investigation into fines hitting vulnerable NHS patients, published on 30 January 2019 by the British Dental Association; what steps his Department is taking to ensure that fear of receiving a fine for ticking the wrong box when claiming for free dental care does not discourage people from low income families from attending the dentist.","true","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","218312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056766","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-02-12","<p>The Department has no plans to review the list of exemptions in the Hunting Act 2004.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-02-12T13:30:57.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056766/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056766/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056766/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-02-07","Hunting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if his Department will review the list of exemptions for hunting with dogs in the Hunting Act 2004 with specific reference to deer hunting.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","218367"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056767","Home Office","false","2019-02-12","<p>The UK’s future skills-based immigration system will make use of the latest digital technology to improve customer experience, increase security and detect abuse. Nearly all applications for individuals seeking to visit, work or study in the UK are now made online. However, under the future system we want to simplify the process further so that all users understand what they need to do and what they are entitled to do.</p><p>We will continue to explore other new technologies to improve application processes, including, for example the ID verification app developed for the EU Settlement Scheme, and we will learn lessons from its use in the EU Settlement Scheme and consider whether it might be appropriate for use in the future system.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-02-12T12:16:42.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056767/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056767/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056767/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-02-07","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent assessment he has made of the potential merits of rolling out the technology used for the EU Settled Status Scheme to other Home Office applications.","false","Biography information for Ellie Reeves","Lewisham West and Penge","Ellie Reeves","218368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056768","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-02-12","<p>All National Health Service dental practices are required to display a poster showing patient charges and to offer patients a free leaflet which sets out in detail who is entitled to free NHS dental services. Information on exemptions and support for people who are on a low income can also be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/healthcosts" target="_blank">www.nhs.uk/healthcosts</a></p><p> </p><p>Eligibility checks are carried out on claims received for exemption from NHS Dental Patient Charges. Where eligibility cannot be verified, patients are asked to confirm their eligibility or to pay the relevant dental charge plus a penalty charge. Patients are, however, able to challenge penalty charges they believe are unjustified.</p><p> </p><p>The Department, NHS Business Services Authority and NHS England have recognised the concern that some patients may not be clear on whether they are exempt from charges and has been working to further improve the information available to patients around eligibility. This includes promoting an easy read patient information booklet, creating an online eligibility checker and developing a national awareness campaign.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","218312","2019-02-12T15:25:29.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056768/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056768/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056768/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-02-07","Dental Services: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the announcement entitled Dentists welcome official investigation into fines hitting vulnerable NHS patients, published by the British Dental Association on 30 January 2019, what steps his Department is taking 