"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-02-14","<p>As required by the Small Business, Enterprise and Employment Act 2015, my rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State will review the operation of the Pubs Code for the period of 21 July 2016 to 31 March 2019. The Government is currently considering the format of the review and will ensure all those with an interest, including tenants and pub companies, have an opportunity to contribute.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst",,"2019-02-14T17:56:48.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801/answer","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801/answer/previousversion/101526","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056801/answer/previousversion/101526",,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-02-07","Public Houses: Codes of Practice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will commission a review of the Pubs Code.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","218388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-02-14","<p>The Government does not hold information the information requested.</p><p>The Government recognises the important role pubs play in local communities. My Rt Hon Friend, the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced at Autumn Budget 2018 that the Government was freezing beer duties for the second consecutive year as beer makes up close to 50% of pub sales. Many pubs are also benefitting from the business rates retail discount, announced at Budget 2018, which cuts bills by one third for retail properties with a rateable value below £51,000 from April 2019, as well as wider reforms and reductions to business rates.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","218390","2019-02-14T17:56:56.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802/answer","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802/answer/previousversion/101527","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056802/answer/previousversion/101527",,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-02-07","Public Houses: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if his Department will review trends in the level of pub closures in (a) the UK, (b) Scotland and (c) Midlothian.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","218389"
