"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2019-02-14","<p>The Government does not hold information the information requested.</p><p>The Government recognises the important role pubs play in local communities. My Rt Hon Friend, the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced at Autumn Budget 2018 that the Government was freezing beer duties for the second consecutive year as beer makes up close to 50% of pub sales. Many pubs are also benefitting from the business rates retail discount, announced at Budget 2018, which cuts bills by one third for retail properties with a rateable value below £51,000 from April 2019, as well as wider reforms and reductions to business rates.</p>","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","218389","2019-02-14T17:56:56.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804/answer","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804/answer","Rochester and Strood","Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804/answer/previousversion/101528","Biography information for Kelly Tolhurst","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1056804/answer/previousversion/101528",,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2019-02-07","Public Houses: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department plans to implement a pubs strategy to tackle the closure of pubs.","false","Biography information for Danielle Rowley","Midlothian","Danielle Rowley","218390"
